<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871217-0086 </DOCNO><HL> Nova Corp. of Alberta SetsIssue of 6.25% Debentures</HL><DD> 12/17/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> NVA.A CANDA </IN><DATELINE> CALGARY, Alberta  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Nova Corp. of Alberta said it agreed to issue 150 million Canadian dollars ($114.6 million) of 6.25% adjustable-rate debentures in a private placement with Alberta Heritage Savings Trust Fund, a provincial government agency.    Nova, a natural gas transmission and petrochemicals concern, said the debentures mature on Feb. 15, 2008 and are convertible into common shares of Nova at 10.70 dollars a share, subject to adjustment in certain events. The issue is subject to regulatory approval.    On the Toronto Stock Exchange, Nova closed yesterday at 10.125 dollars, off 12.5 cents. </TEXT></DOC>